B. Map the images from train folder with train labels to form a DataFrame. [6 Marks]

In [4]:
import cv2
train_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/GL/Projects/CV with CNN/train'
data = []
for folder in sorted(os.listdir(train_path)):
    for i in sorted(os.listdir(train_path +'/'+folder)):
      a = cv2.imread(train_path +'/'+folder + '/' + i) # Storing the image file in a variable a
      a = cv2.resize(a, (128,128)) # Resizing the image
      data.append((folder, i, a)) # Adding folder name (species), image name and image to an array
df = pd.DataFrame(data, columns=['Species', 'Image_Name', 'Image']) # Creating a dataframe using the array

B. Create new CNN architecture to train the model. [4 Marks]

In [18]:
# Initialize the model as Sequential
model1 = Sequential()
# Adding a convolutional layer with 64 filters
model1.add(Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=3, activation='relu', input_shape=(128,128,3)))
# Adding a convolutional layer with 32 filters
model1.add(Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=3, activation='relu'))
# Adding a max pooling layer
model1.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
# Adding a convolutional layer with 32 filters
model1.add(Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=3, activation='relu'))
# Adding a max pooling layer
model1.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
# Adding a dropout layer
model1.add(Dropout(rate=0.2))
# Flattening the layer
model1.add(Flatten())
# Adding a dense layer with relu activation
model1.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))
# Adding the final softmax layer with 12 outputs to match the one hot encoded label vector
model1.add(Dense(12, activation='softmax'))
In [19]:
# Compiling the model
model1.compile(loss="categorical_crossentropy", metrics=["accuracy"], optimizer="adam")

# Using early stopping
callback = tensorflow.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor='val_accuracy', patience=2, min_delta=0.01)
# Training the model
model1.fit(X_train, Y_train, batch_size=32, epochs=10, validation_data=(X_test, Y_test), callbacks=[callback])

def predictor():
    a = np.random.randint(1, 949)
    plt.imshow(X_test[a])
    plt.show()
    Y_pred = np.argmax(model1.predict(X_test), axis=1)
    print('The predicted species of the plant in above image is', label[Y_pred[a]])
    print('The actual Species of plant in above image is', label[np.argmax(Y_test[a])])
